{"type":"message","id":"12c076b6","parentId":"2ff99b0e","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:35:16.502Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Tenemos esto:\n\n- **Objetivo claro**\n  - volver a Atlas un orquestador real, no solo un chat útil\n\n- **Arquitectura base definida**\n  - Atlas = router/orquestador\n  - agentes = especialistas\n  - canales = ejecución real\n\n- **Problema principal identificado**\n  - falta sistema operativo, no más discurso ni más agentes\n\n- **Faltantes clave ya detectados**\n  - router formal\n  - formato fijo de delegación\n  - seguimiento de tareas delegadas\n  - validación real de entrega\n  - estado claro por agente\n  - tablero operativo corto\n  - reglas claras de escalamiento\n\n- **Conclusión operativa**\n  - si cerramos esas piezas, queda **operativo base**\n  - no perfecto, pero sí funcional y confiable para iterar\n\n- **Diagnóstico final**\n  - no falta capacidad\n  - falta convertir criterio en flujo, estructura y control\n\nLa frase corta sería:\n\n**Ya tenemos el mapa. Falta construir el sistema.**\n\nSi quieres, el siguiente paso ya no lo hablamos:  \n**te hago el plan concreto de implementación por prioridad.**","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09d7eb326b5f82d50169cbf7b57ce08191ac3a451029a3a133\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":243,"output":247,"cacheRead":25088,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25578,"cost":{"input":0.0006075000000000001,"output":0.003705,"cacheRead":0.006272,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0105845}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774974899466,"responseId":"resp_09d7eb326b5f82d50169cbf7b4ce888191a01f94f277eece79"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bcd89470","parentId":"12c076b6","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:37:46.025Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"3EB08E5CF083CA1808253F\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"+573183718246\",\n  \"sender\": \"Gustavo Toledo\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Gustavo Toledo (+573183718246)\",\n  \"id\": \"+573183718246\",\n  \"name\": \"Gustavo Toledo\",\n  \"e164\": \"+573183718246\"\n}\n```\n\nQue falta ????????????????????"}],"timestamp":1774975066021}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b984d9e","parentId":"bcd89470","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:37:52.085Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Falta **hacer estas 7 piezas**:\n\n1. **Router formal**  \n   - quién responde qué  \n   - cuándo habla Atlas  \n   - cuándo delega  \n   - cuándo calla\n\n2. **Plantilla fija de delegación**  \n   - objetivo  \n   - acción  \n   - canal  \n   - definición de done  \n   - evidencia\n\n3. **Cola de seguimiento**  \n   - qué se delegó  \n   - a quién  \n   - qué falta  \n   - cuándo revisar\n\n4. **Validación de entrega real**  \n   - no marcar nada como hecho sin confirmar salida real si depende de canal externo\n\n5. **Estado mínimo por agente**  \n   - rol  \n   - prioridades  \n   - restricciones  \n   - bloqueos  \n   - objetivo actual\n\n6. **Tablero operativo corto**  \n   - inbox  \n   - en curso  \n   - waiting  \n   - bloqueados  \n   - decisiones tuyas\n\n7. **Reglas de escalamiento**  \n   - qué resuelvo yo  \n   - qué te subo  \n   - cuándo insistir  \n   - cuándo esperar\n\nEso es lo que falta.  \n**Nada más conceptual: falta implementación.**","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09d7eb326b5f82d50169cbf85ae8fc819181b696e117faef0e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":231,"output":257,"cacheRead":25472,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25960,"cost":{"input":0.0005775,"output":0.003855,"cacheRead":0.0063679999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0108005}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774975066025,"responseId":"resp_09d7eb326b5f82d50169cbf85a567c8191a174b0602f126a42"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5a6df30","parentId":"8b984d9e","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:45:01.055Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"3EB0A3B1AD28BD5C7AF0EE\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"+573183718246\",\n  \"sender\": \"Gustavo Toledo\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Gustavo Toledo (+573183718246)\",\n  \"id\": \"+573183718246\",\n  \"name\": \"Gustavo Toledo\",\n  \"e164\": \"+573183718246\"\n}\n```\n\nsi dale colocalo en ntoion y ve resolviendolos a penas termines el anterior a todo te digo si"}],"timestamp":1774975501052}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4c7eeb6","parentId":"e5a6df30","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:45:04.435Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Voy a revisar el skill de Google Workspace/Notion para usar la integración correcta y luego dejar esto estructurado en tu sistema.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09d7eb326b5f82d50169cbfa0e90e4819189250397ef32c76b\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_EPjEQFEZMujCeIgLOnZ7OAmV|fc_09d7eb326b5f82d50169cbfa0f4cc48191bfd7d2070a23cb49","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\skills\\gog\\SKILL.md"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Gustavo\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\gog\\\\SKILL.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":252,"output":81,"cacheRead":25856,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26189,"cost":{"input":0.00063,"output":0.001215,"cacheRead":0.006464,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008309}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774975501055,"responseId":"resp_09d7eb326b5f82d50169cbfa0da1448191847a7edd9a9ba679"}}
{"type":"message","id":"77c5eba9","parentId":"b4c7eeb6","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:45:04.444Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_EPjEQFEZMujCeIgLOnZ7OAmV|fc_09d7eb326b5f82d50169cbfa0f4cc48191bfd7d2070a23cb49","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: gog\ndescription: Google Workspace CLI for Gmail, Calendar, Drive, Contacts, Sheets, and Docs.\nhomepage: https://gogcli.sh\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"emoji\": \"🎮\",\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"gog\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"brew\",\n              \"kind\": \"brew\",\n              \"formula\": \"steipete/tap/gogcli\",\n              \"bins\": [\"gog\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install gog (brew)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# gog\n\nUse `gog` for Gmail/Calendar/Drive/Contacts/Sheets/Docs. Requires OAuth setup.\n\nSetup (once)\n\n- `gog auth credentials /path/to/client_secret.json`\n- `gog auth add you@gmail.com --services gmail,calendar,drive,contacts,docs,sheets`\n- `gog auth list`\n\nCommon commands\n\n- Gmail search: `gog gmail search 'newer_than:7d' --max 10`\n- Gmail messages search (per email, ignores threading): `gog gmail messages search \"in:inbox from:ryanair.com\" --max 20 --account you@example.com`\n- Gmail send (plain): `gog gmail send --to a@b.com --subject \"Hi\" --body \"Hello\"`\n- Gmail send (multi-line): `gog gmail send --to a@b.com --subject \"Hi\" --body-file ./message.txt`\n- Gmail send (stdin): `gog gmail send --to a@b.com --subject \"Hi\" --body-file -`\n- Gmail send (HTML): `gog gmail send --to a@b.com --subject \"Hi\" --body-html \"<p>Hello</p>\"`\n- Gmail draft: `gog gmail drafts create --to a@b.com --subject \"Hi\" --body-file ./message.txt`\n- Gmail send draft: `gog gmail drafts send <draftId>`\n- Gmail reply: `gog gmail send --to a@b.com --subject \"Re: Hi\" --body \"Reply\" --reply-to-message-id <msgId>`\n- Calendar list events: `gog calendar events <calendarId> --from <iso> --to <iso>`\n- Calendar create event: `gog calendar create <calendarId> --summary \"Title\" --from <iso> --to <iso>`\n- Calendar create with color: `gog calendar create <calendarId> --summary \"Title\" --from <iso> --to <iso> --event-color 7`\n- Calendar update event: `gog calendar update <calendarId> <eventId> --summary \"New Title\" --event-color 4`\n- Calendar show colors: `gog calendar colors`\n- Drive search: `gog drive search \"query\" --max 10`\n- Contacts: `gog contacts list --max 20`\n- Sheets get: `gog sheets get <sheetId> \"Tab!A1:D10\" --json`\n- Sheets update: `gog sheets update <sheetId> \"Tab!A1:B2\" --values-json '[[\"A\",\"B\"],[\"1\",\"2\"]]' --input USER_ENTERED`\n- Sheets append: `gog sheets append <sheetId> \"Tab!A:C\" --values-json '[[\"x\",\"y\",\"z\"]]' --insert INSERT_ROWS`\n- Sheets clear: `gog sheets clear <sheetId> \"Tab!A2:Z\"`\n- Sheets metadata: `gog sheets metadata <sheetId> --json`\n- Docs export: `gog docs export <docId> --format txt --out /tmp/doc.txt`\n- Docs cat: `gog docs cat <docId>`\n\nCalendar Colors\n\n- Use `gog calendar colors` to see all available event colors (IDs 1-11)\n- Add colors to events with `--event-color <id>` flag\n- Event color IDs (from `gog calendar colors` output):\n  - 1: #a4bdfc\n  - 2: #7ae7bf\n  - 3: #dbadff\n  - 4: #ff887c\n  - 5: #fbd75b\n  - 6: #ffb878\n  - 7: #46d6db\n  - 8: #e1e1e1\n  - 9: #5484ed\n  - 10: #51b749\n  - 11: #dc2127\n\nEmail Formatting\n\n- Prefer plain text. Use `--body-file` for multi-paragraph messages (or `--body-file -` for stdin).\n- Same `--body-file` pattern works for drafts and replies.\n- `--body` does not unescape `\\n`. If you need inline newlines, use a heredoc or `$'Line 1\\n\\nLine 2'`.\n- Use `--body-html` only when you need rich formatting.\n- HTML tags: `<p>` for paragraphs, `<br>` for line breaks, `<strong>` for bold, `<em>` for italic, `<a href=\"url\">` for links, `<ul>`/`<li>` for lists.\n- Example (plain text via stdin):\n\n  ```bash\n  gog gmail send --to recipient@example.com \\\n    --subject \"Meeting Follow-up\" \\\n    --body-file - <<'EOF'\n  Hi Name,\n\n  Thanks for meeting today. Next steps:\n  - Item one\n  - Item two\n\n  Best regards,\n  Your Name\n  EOF\n  ```\n\n- Example (HTML list):\n  ```bash\n  gog gmail send --to recipient@example.com \\\n    --subject \"Meeting Follow-up\" \\\n    --body-html \"<p>Hi Name,</p><p>Thanks for meeting today. Here are the next steps:</p><ul><li>Item one</li><li>Item two</li></ul><p>Best regards,<br>Your Name</p>\"\n  ```\n\nNotes\n\n- Set `GOG_ACCOUNT=you@gmail.com` to avoid repeating `--account`.\n- For scripting, prefer `--json` plus `--no-input`.\n- Sheets values can be passed via `--values-json` (recommended) or as inline rows.\n- Docs supports export/cat/copy. In-place edits require a Docs API client (not in gog).\n- Confirm before sending mail or creating events.\n- `gog gmail search` returns one row per thread; use `gog gmail messages search` when you need every individual email returned separately.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774975504442}}
{"type":"message","id":"3c4bec3b","parentId":"77c5eba9","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:45:21.065Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Voy a crear el plan en Notion usando la API que ya tienes configurada, y dejarlo como una lista secuencial para ir resolviéndolo uno por uno.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09d7eb326b5f82d50169cbfa11f2088191a26b5af1c67adfe3\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_nWIyCQnqltCw87ByPWhYLXG1|fc_09d7eb326b5f82d50169cbfa12d5b08191a6e79fb60cea1d41","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$ErrorActionPreference='Stop'\n$headers = @{\n  'Authorization' = \"Bearer $env:NOTION_TOKEN\"\n  'Notion-Version' = '2022-06-28'\n  'Content-Type' = 'application/json'\n}\n$body = @{\n  parent = @{ page_id = '32f0a0b1-97cc-8115-9e62-ec8765ad533c' }\n  properties = @{\n    title = @(@{ text = @{ content = 'Plan operativo Atlas - Autonomía con agentes' } })\n  }\n  children = @(\n    @{\n      object='block'; type='paragraph';\n      paragraph=@{ rich_text=@(@{ type='text'; text=@{ content='Objetivo: volver a Atlas operativo base como orquestador real. Se resuelve en secuencia: no se salta al siguiente punto sin cerrar el anterior.' } }) }\n    },\n    @{\n      object='block'; type='bulleted_list_item';\n      bulleted_list_item=@{ rich_text=@(@{ type='text'; text=@{ content='1. Router formal' } }) }\n    },\n    @{\n      object='block'; type='bulleted_list_item';\n      bulleted_list_item=@{ rich_text=@(@{ type='text'; text=@{ content='2. Plantilla fija de delegación' } }) }\n    },\n    @{\n      object='block'; type='bulleted_list_item';\n      bulleted_list_item=@{ rich_text=@(@{ type='text'; text=@{ content='3. Cola de seguimiento' } }) }\n    },\n    @{\n      object='block'; type='bulleted_list_item';\n      bulleted_list_item=@{ rich_text=@(@{ type='text'; text=@{ content='4. Validación de entrega real' } }) }\n    },\n    @{\n      object='block'; type='bulleted_list_item';\n      bulleted_list_item=@{ rich_text=@(@{ type='text'; text=@{ content='5. Estado mínimo por agente' } }) }\n    },\n    @{\n      object='block'; type='bulleted_list_item';\n      bulleted_list_item=@{ rich_text=@(@{ type='text'; text=@{ content='6. Tablero operativo corto' } }) }\n    },\n    @{\n      object='block'; type='bulleted_list_item';\n      bulleted_list_item=@{ rich_text=@(@{ type='text'; text=@{ content='7. Reglas de escalamiento' } }) }\n    },\n    @{\n      object='block'; type='paragraph';\n      paragraph=@{ rich_text=@(@{ type='text'; text=@{ content='Criterio de ejecución: Atlas resuelve uno por uno y te va diciendo para aprobar o ajustar.' } }) }\n    }\n  )\n}\n$json = $body | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 20\nInvoke-RestMethod -Method Post -Uri 'https://api.notion.com/v1/pages' -Headers $headers -Body $json | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 10","workdir":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"$ErrorActionPreference='Stop'\\n$headers = @{\\n  'Authorization' = \\\"Bearer $env:NOTION_TOKEN\\\"\\n  'Notion-Version' = '2022-06-28'\\n  'Content-Type' = 'application/json'\\n}\\n$body = @{\\n  parent = @{ page_id = '32f0a0b1-97cc-8115-9e62-ec8765ad533c' }\\n  properties = @{\\n    title = @(@{ text = @{ content = 'Plan operativo Atlas - Autonomía con agentes' } })\\n  }\\n  children = @(\\n    @{\\n      object='block'; type='paragraph';\\n      paragraph=@{ rich_text=@(@{ type='text'; text=@{ content='Objetivo: volver a Atlas operativo base como orquestador real. Se resuelve en secuencia: no se salta al siguiente punto sin cerrar el anterior.' } }) }\\n    },\\n    @{\\n      object='block'; type='bulleted_list_item';\\n      bulleted_list_item=@{ rich_text=@(@{ type='text'; text=@{ content='1. Router formal' } }) }\\n    },\\n    @{\\n      object='block'; type='bulleted_list_item';\\n      bulleted_list_item=@{ rich_text=@(@{ type='text'; text=@{ content='2. Plantilla fija de delegación' } }) }\\n    },\\n    @{\\n      object='block